{
  "stem": "4361.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, we were told that they were just resettled in Poland to their country of origin, except that some rumors began to seep through that this transport was murdered somewhere on the way.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I think, As I look back now, I think that was the first harbinger of things to come.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I tell you, nobody really registered.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Nobody registered because it was too horrendous to contemplate that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This was in 1942.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Soon thereafter, certain laws were put in effect and this is where I personally was touched.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Children, Jewish children could not attend high school-- and that was called [GERMAN], unless their parents, their father, had some sort of a decoration during the first war, First World War, as being part of the Austro-Hungarian regime and being in the army.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Well, my father was not in the army, but my uncle was, my uncle who forbade contraband.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And he, in fact, got some sort of a gold decoration from the Hungarian regime during the First World War because of some act of heroism.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He saved, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he went to try to intercede that I should be permitted to go to school because I was a good student, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "No way.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was out, but some Jewish girls could still go because their fathers did have that decoration.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What happened to me then was that, at that point, the Hungarian government permitted two-- accredited-- two Jewish high schools, one in Budapest and one in Kolozsvar.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But again, it was very difficult to get in because, as you can imagine, every Jewish child whose father was not decorated by the Hungarians during the First World War wanted to go to school.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there was a very heavy selection process.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I did get in.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
